PHONE_REDACTEDT10:PORT:PORT.458489Z	   10 Query	insert into daily_analysis_reports (analysis_confidence,analysis_scope_note,day,executive_summary,generated_at,misconfiguration_signals,system_behavior_analysis,user_behavior_analysis) values ('The analysis is based on the provided data and assumes that the system handled all lead submission attempts. However, the absence of rate limit failures by final page may indicate an issue with tracking such errors in the current setup.','This analysis covers a single calendar day (March 17, 2026 IST), focusing on lead submission behavior, user activity patterns, system constraints, potential misconfigurations, and temporal trends.','PHONE_REDACTED','On the day of March 17, 2026 (IST), there were a total of 192 lead submission attempts, out of which 129 were successful, accounting for a success ratio of 67.19%. Notably, duplicate leads and rate limit exceeded errors were the most frequent failure reasons.','PHONE_REDACTED:PORT:PORT.448337','The high frequency of duplicate leads suggests potential misconfiguration in lead storage or duplication prevention mechanisms.','The system processed 192 lead submissions primarily through the website form, totaling 181 attempts. Analyzing the failure reasons, duplicate leads were most common at 52 occurrences, and rate limit exceeded errors accounted for 11 failures.','Two users, EMAIL_REDACTED and EMAIL_REDACTED, showed high activity with 114 and 78 attempts respectively. EMAIL_REDACTED had a higher success rate than EMAIL_REDACTED, with a failure ratio of 30.77% compared to 34.21%.')
